<TITLE> CID may look into Bashundhara fire </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 22 (bdnew24.com)  The government's committee investigating the Bashundhara City fire may suggest that the CID try to dig up what caused the Mar 13 devastating blaze, an official said. The three-strong panel headed by joint home secretary Iqbal Khan Chowdhury is scheduled to file their findings Monday. The investigators however have found evidence of neglect that caused the fire to spread out, an official involved in the investigation told bdnews24.com, on condition of anonymity. He added a lot more time was needed to find out the cause of the fire despite having quizzed several people. The committee may recommend that CID investigate the case, he said. The probe did not find any evidence of 'sabotage' or arson, the official added. The floor where accounts had been kept was unaffected. "If it was sabotage that floor could have been burnt down," he said
